headline: CFPB expands oversight to PayPal and Block, says New Street
summary: New Street says the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau’s finalized rule that it will soon supervise non-bank firms that offer financial services includes PayPal (PYPL), Block (SQ), Apple (AAPL), Google (GOOG, GOOGL) Amazon (AMZN) and Zelle. Unsurprisingly, banks supported these actions after facing competitive pressure from tech firms moving into financial services, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
